info.title: Gabon API
info.description:
# Introduction
The API allows access to the management of the resources

# Overview
Almost all endpoints require a valid JWT token. 
There are 4 routes accessible without token : 

- /api/users/login
- /api/users/register
- /api/users/password
- /api/users/forgot 

Every request must contain the following Headers :
```
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
```

When you call endpoints which list resources (eg. List Users, List permits) you can use 
GET parametes `page` and `search` for pagination and search. 
Examples :
```
GET /api/users?page=2
GET /api/users?search=admin
```


# Authentication
The token must be used in Headers Authorization field as `Bearer <token here>`

Alternative the token can be sent in body request or as URL parameter under `jwt` key.

# Error Codes

404 - not found
500 - server error

# Rate limit
There is no limit to the number of requests an user can send.

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: How many results per page (optional). Default: 20

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Sort order: asc or dsc (optional). Default: asc. For multiple fields to sort use "|" as separator. Ex: asc|dsc

parameters.name: sort_fields
parameters.description: Fields to sort (optional). Default: Id. For multiple fields use "|" as separator. Ex: Id|Approved

post.description:
If the user exists, he will receive an email with an activation code.

He will use this code in a request to "Change password" endpoint.

put.description:
Update user with id 17.

You can update user's firstname and lastname.

delete.description:
Delete User id 13.

We are using "Soft Deletes" so the user isn't acctually deleted.

get.description: Get a list of items for a permission by `mobile_id` or `permit_id`

post.description: Store on item for a permit by `mobile_id` or `permit_id`

get.description: GeoJson used for OpenLayers in order to show on the map the geometry for the transport permits.

post.description:
Tracking the permit (transportation) for the mobile application.

Can be sent one or multiple points (coordinates), each with a datetime format "Y-m-d h:i:s"

Each permit has an internal id "mobile_id". This id should be used in the url `/api/permits/{mobile_id}/tracking` when sending the coordinates for a transportation

get.description:
Endpoint to get all translation keys.

`mobile` optional parameter to get tranlsation keys for mobile or not. If missing you will get all translation keys.

parameters.name: mobile
parameters.description: Optional. Can have values: 1 or 0. If missing you will get all keys
